SIMPLE: knock-out_drops
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: knock-out drops
<hw>knock-out drops</hw></mhw> <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <def>Drops of any drug, used to a person to fall asleep or
become unconscious or stupefied for the purpose of robbery, etc.; they
are usually mixed into a drink so that the person consuming it does so
unknowingly. One compound used for this purpose is <styp><er>chloral
hydrate</er></styp>.</def> <mark>[Slang, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knockstone</ent>⟦br⟧
